episodes.title: Queens Ruveal
episodes.plot: An introduction to the new queens, hosted by Sasha Velour.

episodes.title: 10s Across the Board
episodes.plot: Fourteen queens compete in a recreation of the very first challenge in RuPaul's Drag Race history; Christina Aguilera guest judges.

episodes.title: PharmaRusical
episodes.plot: The remaining queens perform a two-team, two-part performance of PharmaRusical.

episodes.title: Tap That App
episodes.plot: In this challenge, Rupaul separates the queens into three groups, each with a different fictional dating app to promote; Courtney Love and Nico Tortorella guest judge.

episodes.title: The Last Ball on Earth
episodes.plot: In the first Ball challenge of the season, the queens construct three looks inspired by the effects of global warming on society and the environment.

episodes.title: The Bossy Rossy Show
episodes.plot: In a mock talk-show, the queens compete and play out different talk-show archetypes; Carrie Preston and Shania Twain guest judge.

episodes.title: DragCon Panel Extravaganza
episodes.plot: The queens have to produce and host their very own Drag Con panels on Makeup, Hair and Body. Husband and wife duo behind the Oscar nominated film, The Big Sick, Kumail Nanjiani and Emily Gordon guest judge.

episodes.title: Snatch Game
episodes.plot: The queens tackle their season's Snatch Game.

episodes.title: Cher: The Unauthorized Rusical
episodes.plot: In "Cher: The Unauthorized Rusical" the queens sing live in a musical about Cher's decade spanning career; Billy Eichner and Andrew Rannells guest judge.

episodes.title: Breastworld
episodes.plot: "Broad City" stars Ilana Glazer and Abbi Jacobson guest judge on this week's episode. A parody of "Westworld" and the acting challenge of season ten.

episodes.title: Social Media Kings Into Queens
episodes.plot: The queens makeover social media "kings into their drag sisters, as well as take part in a home-made music video. Hip hop artist Lizzo and star of 13 Reasons Why, Miles Heizer guest judge.

episodes.title: Evil Twins
episodes.plot: The top five queens must present two sides of themselves in a ball, a good twin and an evil twin.

episodes.title: American
episodes.plot: The queens record verses to Rupaul's track "American", perform it on the main stage and be interviewed by Rupaul and Michelle Visage for their podcast to decide who will go on to the finale; choreographer Todrick Hall guest judges.

episodes.title: Reunited
episodes.plot: Before the winner of season ten is crowned, the queens return to spill the tea.

episodes.title: Grand Finale
episodes.plot: The winner of Rupaul's Drag Race season ten is crowned after winning the second ever lip sync for the crown.
